episodes.title: Engineering
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry hosts another edition of the quiz show that mines the world of trivia. Alan Davies, Jimmy Carr, Rob Brydon and Bill Bailey are the guests trying to avoid going loco as they tackle tough teasers on the subject of engineering.

episodes.title: Electricity
episodes.plot: Alan Davies, Jo Brand, Sean Lock and Rich Hall tackle some electrifying questions from host Stephen Fry.

episodes.title: Eating
episodes.plot: Alan Davies, Jimmy Carr, Phill Jupitus and Johnny Vegas sink their teeth in to some delicious questions on eating.

episodes.title: Exploration
episodes.plot: Bill Bailey, Rich Hall, Sean Lock and Alan Davies answer questions on some quite interesting explorations.

episodes.title: Europe
episodes.plot: Phill Jupitus, Dara O'Briain, David Mitchell and Alan Davies get continental in this Europe themed episode.

episodes.title: Everything, Etc.
episodes.plot: Alan Davies, Clive Anderson, Jeremy Clarkson and Vic Reeves discuss absolutely everything.

episodes.title: Espionage
episodes.plot: Host Stephen Fry edgily exposes Espionage with Jo Brand, Vic Reeves, Clive Anderson and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Eyes and Ears
episodes.plot: Host Stephen Fry is all Eyes and Ears with guests Phill Jupitus, Jimmy Carr, David Mitchell and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Entertainment
episodes.plot: Host Stephen Fry is joined by Bill Bailey, Pudsey Bear, Jo Brand, Jeremy Clarkson and Alan Davies to discuss Entertainment in a special Children in Need edition.

episodes.title: England
episodes.plot: Host Stephen Fry is joined by Sean Lock, Phill Jupitus, Charlie Higson and Alan Davies to get to grips with the subject of England.

episodes.title: Endings
episodes.plot: Host Stephen Fry endlessly elongates endings with panellists Jimmy Carr, Doon Mackichan, Dara Oi Briain and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Empire
episodes.plot: Masterful host Stephen Fry rules the really rather interesting quiz with an iron fist as he questions guests Alan Davies, Bill Bailey, Sean Lock and Jo Brand on the subject of empires. Will the teasing questions leave them in a state?

episodes.title: Elephants
episodes.plot: As per request of "young Alan Davies", Santa, A.K.A Stephen Fry, brings him a compilation show of some of the funniest moments of the season, with some unseen footage.
